\begin_layout Itemize
Case I: Social and private value rankings align
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Pure market case 
\begin_inset Formula $H=h=y_{H}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $L=l=y_{L}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Choosing an efficient contractor: 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 types are more efficient, make more money 
\begin_inset Formula $h>l$
\end_inset

.
 Also probably 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{H}=h$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{L}=l$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allocating import licenses: 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 types make most profits.
 But credit constraints might bind: 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{H}<h=H$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{L}<l=L$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
